-- Avis rental car reports narrow profit
-- 
-- Wed May 2, 2007 5:03pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/02/us-avis-results-idUSWEN755420070502

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Car rental company Avis Budget Group Inc. CAR.N reported a sharply narrowed quarterly net profit on Wednesday as the company incurred costs related to due to its spinoff from Cendant Corp. 

 The company, which comprises the remainder of leisure conglomerate Cendant Corp. after spinning off or selling its other units, reported net profit of $13 million, or 12 cents per share, compared with a profit of $70 million, or $70 cents per share, in the year-ago quarter. The company's income from continuing operations was 12 cents per share. Wall Street analysts had expected the company's earnings per share of nil in the quarter, according to Reuters Estimates. Avis said its revenue increased 2 percent to $1.4 billion. The company said it expects its revenue an income to increase in 2007, compared with 2006. Last year, Cendant sold its Travelport unit to private equity investors and spun off its real estate and hospitality businesses.